  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Response Mongolia Feb 2010</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since December 2009, Mongolia has been experiencing a severe winter locally known as dzud, a continuous heavy snowfall combined with extreme cold. The average temperature in northern Mongolia has dropped to -35 degrees Celsius, with temperatures in the rest of country hovering between -22 to -17 degrees Celsius. The government reports that 19 of the 21 provinces are suffering from the harsh conditions. Funding under this initiative provides support to humanitarian agencies - UN and INGOs - to respond to the Mongolian Cold Wave. The total value of this initiative is $1.0 million to be expensed during the 2009-10 financial year.</narrative>
  </description>
